вҖ»вҖ»
# board-prep вҖ” Dark Factory rung 0 (onboarding), GitHub path

Idempotent, ASSISTED-MODE onboarding that prepares a repo + its GitHub Project for the
Dark Factory ladder. GENERIC: runs against the CALLER's repo (the run's working dir) and a
GitHub Project you pass by number. Pure bash + `gh`, deterministic, fail-closed вҖ” no LLM,
no budget.

WHY this exists (the researched gap): a GitHub Projects v2 **template** reproduces board
STRUCTURE (the Status single-select + its options, other custom fields, views) but it does
NOT carry вҖ” and no project copy/template ever can вҖ” the two things onboarding actually
needs wired per repo:
  вҖў repo-scoped LABELS  (labels live on the repository, not the project), and
  вҖў the AUTO-ADD workflow (explicitly excluded from copy/template; has no public API).
So this workflow fills exactly that gap: it creates the 9 lifecycle labels on the repo,
links the project to the repo, verifies the project carries the dark-factory field schema
(from the Skylence project template), and prints the two MANUAL UI steps the API can't do.

Two vocabularies it reconciles:
  вҖў LABELS  (repo, what the ladder rungs key off):  data/labels.yaml вҖ” triaging В· accepted В·
    ready-for-sky В· in-progress В· needs-review В· approved В· needs-fix В· rejected В· escalated
  вҖў COLUMNS (project Status field, the human Kanban, from org project #1 "Skylence project
    template"):  Icebox В· Backlog В· Ready В· Agent Running В· Awaiting Review В·
    Revisions Requested В· Done   (+ Priority / Size / Idea Stage / Bug Stage custom fields)
The labelвҶ’column mapping lives in the `darkfactory-onboarding` skill and in the report.

  (sky run board-prep --var project=<n> [--var owner=<org-or-user>] [--var repo=<owner/name>])
        в”Ӯ
        в–ј
   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  bash + gh. Resolve OWNER/REPO (--var repo or `gh repo view`), require
   в”Ӯ  preflight   в”Ӯ  --var project=<n>, verify project access (needs gh `project` scope).
   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  Fail-closed: any missing вҶ’ exit 1. Emits {owner,repo,project} JSON.
        в”Ӯ depends_on (preflight)
        в”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
        в–ј               в–ј               в–ј
   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
   в”Ӯ  labels  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ  link    в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   fields     в”Ӯ  bash + gh, all idempotent / read-only:
   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  labels = `gh label create --force` Г—9;
   create 9        `gh project    verify Status options + the custom fields exist on the
   lifecycle       link` the      linked project (advisory вҖ” never mutates the project).
   labels on       project to
   the repo        the repo
        в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
                        в”Ӯ depends_on [labels, link, fields], trigger_rule all_done
                        в–ј
                 в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  bash. Summarize what was done + print the 2 MANUAL UI
                 в”Ӯ   report     в”Ӯ  steps with no API: (1) enable Auto-add filtered to this
                 в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  repo, (2) wire the labelвҶ’Status column automation.

SAFETY:
  - Idempotent: `gh label create --force` upserts; re-linking an already-linked project is a no-op.
  - Read-only on the project's fields (the `fields` node only verifies; it never edits the schema).
  - Fail-closed: a missing --var project, an unresolvable repo, or no project access aborts at preflight.
  - Uses the run environment's ambient `gh` auth; needs the `project` scope for the project calls.
вҖ»вҖ»

вҠ•metaвҠ•
name = "board-prep"
description = "Dark Factory rung 0 (onboarding, GitHub): idempotently create the 9 lifecycle labels (data/labels.yaml) on the caller's repo, link a GitHub Project to the repo, verify the project carries the dark-factory field schema (Status: IceboxвҶ’Done plus Priority/Size/Idea Stage/Bug Stage, from the Skylence project template), and print the manual UI steps the GitHub API cannot do (auto-add workflow + labelвҶ’Status automation). A project template carries board STRUCTURE but never repo labels or auto-add wiring вҖ” this fills that gap. Pure bash + gh, deterministic, fail-closed, idempotent. Fire via: sky run board-prep --var project=<project-number> [--var owner=<org-or-user>] [--var repo=<owner/name>]"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
вҠ•вҠ•

вҖ»вҖ»
Step 1 вҖ” preflight. DETERMINISTIC bash + gh, no LLM. Resolve the target and fail-closed before
any mutation. OWNER/REPO come from --var (вҶ’ $SKY_OWNER / $SKY_REPO) or, when REPO is unset, from
`gh repo view` in the working dir; OWNER defaults to REPO's owner. PROJECT ($SKY_PROJECT, a
GitHub Project NUMBER) is REQUIRED. Project access is checked with `gh project view` (which needs
the `project` auth scope). Emits ONE JSON line {owner,repo,project} consumed downstream via jq.
{{var}} is NOT used вҖ” bash reads the $SKY_* env channel directly and shell-quotes every expansion.
вҖ»вҖ»

В§preflightВ§
bash_file = "./scripts/preflight.sh"
В§В§

вҖ»вҖ»
Step 2 вҖ” labels. DETERMINISTIC bash + gh, no LLM. Create the 9 repo-scoped lifecycle labels from
data/labels.yaml on the target repo. `gh label create --force` is an idempotent UPSERT (creates, or
overwrites color/description if the label already exists), so re-runs are safe. Labels are the one
thing no project template can ever provide (they are repo-scoped). REPO comes from preflight's JSON.
вҖ»вҖ»

В§labelsВ§
depends_on = ["preflight"]
bash_file = "./scripts/labels.sh"
В§В§

вҖ»вҖ»
Step 3 вҖ” link. DETERMINISTIC bash + gh, no LLM. Link the project to the repo so the board can pull
the repo's items. `gh project link` is idempotent in effect вҖ” an already-linked project is reported,
not treated as an error. OWNER/REPO/PROJECT come from preflight's JSON.
вҖ»вҖ»

В§linkВ§
depends_on = ["preflight"]
bash_file = "./scripts/link.sh"
В§В§

вҖ»вҖ»
Step 4 вҖ” fields. DETERMINISTIC bash + gh, no LLM. READ-ONLY verification: does the linked project
carry the dark-factory field schema from the Skylence project template? Reports any missing custom
field (Status / Priority / Size / Idea Stage / Bug Stage) and any missing Status COLUMN option
(Icebox вҖҰ Done). It NEVER edits the project вҖ” creating/altering single-select fields is the
template's job; this only tells you whether the template was applied. grep is a substring check
(advisory). FL falls back to {} if the field-list call has no access.
вҖ»вҖ»

В§fieldsВ§
depends_on = ["preflight"]
bash_file = "./scripts/fields.sh"
В§В§

вҖ»вҖ»
Step 5 вҖ” report. DETERMINISTIC bash, no LLM. The single leaf вҖ” depends on labels+link+fields with
trigger_rule all_done so it always summarizes. Echoes each upstream node's output, then prints the
two MANUAL Projects-UI steps that have NO public API: (1) enable Auto-add filtered to this repo,
(2) wire the labelвҶ’Status column automation (the mapping the ladder + the human board share).
вҖ»вҖ»

В§reportВ§
depends_on = ["labels", "link", "fields"]
trigger_rule = "all_done"
bash_file = "./scripts/report.sh"
В§В§
